label: unit
definition: A unit of measurement is a standardized quantity of a physical quality.

label: length unit
definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the distance between two points.

label: mass unit
definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the amount of matter/energy of a physical object.

label: time unit
definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the dimension in which events occur in sequence.

label: electric current unit
definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the flow of electric charge.

label: temperature unit
definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the average kinetic energy of the particles in a sample of matter.

label: substance unit
definition: A unit which is a standardised quantity of an element or compound with uniform composition.

label: luminous intensity unit
definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the wavelength-weighted power emitted by a light source in a particular direction.

label: meter
definition: A length unit which is equal to the length of the path traveled by light in vacuum during a time interval of 1/299 792 458 of a second.

label: kilogram
definition: A mass unit which is equal to the mass of the International Prototype Kilogram kept by the BIPM at Svres, France.

label: second
definition: A time unit which is equal to the duration of 9 192 631 770 periods of the radiation corresponding to the transition between the two hyperfine levels of the ground state of the caesium 133 atom.

label: ampere
definition: An electric current unit which is equal to the constant current which, if maintained in two straight parallel conductors of infinite length, of negligible circular cross-section, and placed 1 m apart in vacuum, would produce between these conductors a force equal to 2 x 10^[-7] newton per meter of length.

label: kelvin
definition: A thermodynamic temperature unit which is equal to the fraction 1/273.16 of the thermodynamic temperature of the triple point of water.

label: mole
definition: A substance unit which is equal to the amount of substance of a molecular system which contains as many elementary entities as there are atoms in 0.012 kilogram of carbon 12.

label: candela
definition: A luminous intensity unit which equal to the luminous intensity, in a given direction, of a source that emits monochromatic radiation of frequency 540 x 1012 hertz and that has a radiant intensity in that direction of 1/683 watt per steradian.

label: centimeter
definition: A length unit which is equal to one hundredth of a meter or 10^[-2] m.

label: millimeter
definition: A length unit which is equal to one thousandth of a meter or 10^[-3] m.

label: micrometer
definition: A length unit which is equal to one millionth of a meter or 10^[-6] m.

label: nanometer
definition: A length unit which is equal to one thousandth of one millionth of a meter or 10^[-9] m.

label: angstrom
definition: A length unit which is equal to 10 [-10] m.

label: picometer
definition: A length unit which is equal to 10^[-12] m.

label: gram
definition: A mass unit which is equal to one thousandth of a kilogram or 10^[-3] kg.

label: milligram
definition: A mass unit which is equal to one thousandth of a gram or 10^[-3] g.

label: microgram
definition: A mass unit which is equal to one millionth of a gram or 10^[-6] g.

label: nanogram
definition: A mass unit which is equal to one thousandth of one millionth of a gram or 10^[-9] g.

label: picogram
definition: A mass unit which is equal to 10^[-12] g.

label: femtogram
definition: A mass unit which is equal to 10^[-15] g.

label: degree Celsius
definition: A temperature unit which is equal to one kelvin degree. However, they have their zeros at different points. The centigrade scale has its zero at 273.15 K.

label: millisecond
definition: A time unit which is equal to one thousandth of a second or 10^[-3] s.

label: microsecond
definition: A time unit which is equal to one millionth of a second or 10^[-6] s.

label: picosecond
definition: A time unit which is equal to 10^[-12] s.

label: minute
definition: A time unit which is equal to 60 seconds.

label: hour
definition: A time unit which is equal to 3600 seconds or 60 minutes.

label: day
definition: A time unit which is equal to 24 hours.

label: week
definition: A time unit which is equal to 7 days.

label: month
definition: A time unit which is approximately equal to the length of time of one of cycle of the moon's phases which in science is taken to be equal to 30 days.

label: year
definition: A time unit which is equal to 12 months which in science is taken to be equal to 365.25 days.

label: milliampere
definition: An electric current unit current which is equal to one thousandth of an ampere or 10^[-3] A.

label: microampere
definition: An electric current unit current which is equal to one millionth of an ampere or 10^[-6] A.

label: micromole
definition: A substance unit equal to a millionth of a mol or 10^[-6] mol.

label: millimole
definition: A substance unit equal to a thousandth of a mol or 10^[-3] mol.

label: nanomole
definition: A substance unit equal to one thousandth of one millionth of a mole or 10^[-9] mol.

label: picomole
definition: A substance unit equal to 10^[-12] mol.

label: femtomole
definition: A substance unit equal to 10^[-15] mol.

label: attomole
definition: A substance unit equal to 10^[-18] mol.

label: base unit
definition: A unit which is one of a particular measure to which all measures of that type can be related.

label: area unit
definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the amount of a 2-dimensional flat surface.

label: acceleration unit
definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the rate of change of velocity in either speed or direction.

label: angular velocity unit
definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the rate of angular movement about an axis; the angle rotated in a given time.

label: angular acceleration unit
definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the rate of change of angular velocity.

label: concentration unit
definition: A unit which represents a standard measurement of how much of a given substance there is mixed with another substance.

label: mass density unit
definition: A density unit which is a standard measure of the mass of a substance in a given volume.

label: luminance unit
definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the luminous intensity impinging on a given area.

label: area density unit
definition: A density unit which is a standard measure of the mass exerting an influence on a given area.

label: molar mass unit
definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the mass of a homogeneous substance containing 6.02 x 1023 atoms or molecules.

label: molar volume unit
definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the volume of a homogeneous substance containing 6.02 x 1023 atoms or molecules.

label: momentum unit
definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the quantity of motion measured by the product of mass and velocity.

label: rotational frequency unit
definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the number of rotations in a given time.

label: specific volume unit
definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the volume of a given mass of substance (the reciprocal of density).

label: speed/velocity unit
definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the rate of movement. Speed is measured in the same physical units of measurement as velocity, but does not contain the element of direction that velocity has. Speed is thus the magnitude component of velocity.

label: unit of molarity
definition: A concentration unit which is a standard measure of the number of moles of a given substance per liter of solution.

label: molar
definition: A unit of concentration which expresses a concentration of 1 mole of solute per liter of solution (mol/L).

label: millimolar
definition: A unit of molarity which is equal to one thousandth of a molar or 10^[-3] M.

label: micromolar
definition: A unit of molarity which is equal to one millionth of a molar or 10^[-6] M.

label: nanomolar
definition: A unit of molarity which is equal to one thousandth of one millionth of a molar or 10^[-9] M.

label: picomolar
definition: A unit of molarity which is equal to 10^[-12] M.

label: unit of molality
definition: A concentration unit which is a standard measure of the number of moles of a given substance per kilogram of solvent.

label: molal
definition: A unit of concentration which expresses a concentration of a solution of 1 mole per kilogram of solvent (mol/kg).

label: millimolal
definition: A molality unit which is equal to one thousandth of a molal or 10^[-3] m.

label: micromolal
definition: A molality unit which is equal to one millionth of a molal or 10^[-6] m.

label: nanomolal
definition: A molality unit which is equal to one thousandth of one millionth of a molal or 10^[-9] m.

label: picomolal
definition: A molality unit which is equal to 10^[-12] m.

label: femtomolar
definition: A unit of molarity which is equal to 10^[-15] M.

label: unit of normality
definition: A unit of concentration which highlights the chemical nature of salts.

label: normal
definition: A unit of concentration which is one gram equivalent of a solute per liter of solution. A gram equivalent weight or equivalent is a measure of the reactive capacity of a given molecule.

label: mole fraction
definition: A concentration unit which denotes the number of moles of solute as a proportion of the total number of moles in a solution.

label: meter per second per second
definition: An acceleration unit which is equal to the acceleration an object changing its velocity by 1meter/s over a time period that equals one second.

label: radian per second per second
definition: An angular unit acceleration which is equal to the angular acceleration of an object changing its angular velocity by 1rad/s over a time period that equals one second.

label: radian per second
definition: An angular unit velocity which is equal to about 9.54930 rpm (revolutions per minute).

label: square meter
definition: An area unit which is equal to an area enclosed by a square with sides each 1 meter long.

label: square centimeter
definition: An area unit which is equal to one ten thousandth of a square meter or 10^[-4] m^[2].

label: square millimeter
definition: An area unit which is equal to one millionth of a square meter or 10^[-6] m^[2].

label: kilogram per cubic meter
definition: A mass unit density which is equal to mass of an object in kilograms divided by the volume in cubic meters.

label: gram per cubic centimeter
definition: A mass unit density which is equal to mass of an object in grams divided by the volume in cubic centimeters.

label: candela per square meter
definition: A luminance unit which is equal to a luminous intensity of one candela radiating from a surface whose area is one square meter.

label: kilogram per square meter
definition: An area density unit which is equal to the mass of an object in kilograms divided by the surface area in meters squared.

label: kilogram per mole
definition: A molar mass unit which is equal to one kilogram of mass of one mole of chemical element or chemical compound.

label: gram per mole
definition: A molar mass unit which is equal to one gram of mass of one mole of chemical element or chemical compound.

label: cubic meter per mole
definition: A molar volume unit which is equal to 1 cubic meter occupied by one mole of a substance in the form of a solid, liquid, or gas.

label: cubic centimeter per mole
definition: A molar volume unit which is equal to 1 cubic centimeter occupied by one mole of a substance in the form of a solid, liquid, or gas.

label: kilogram meter per second
definition: A momentum unit which is equal to the momentum of a one kilogram mass object with a speed of one meter per second.

label: turns per second
definition: A rotational frequency unit which is equal to the number complete turn in a period of time that equals to 1 second.

label: cubic meter per kilogram
definition: A specific volume unit which is equal to one cubic meter volume occupied by one kilogram of a particular substance.

label: meter per second
definition: A speed/velocity unit which is equal to the speed of an object traveling 1 meter distance in one second.

label: volume unit
definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the amount of space occupied by any substance, whether solid, liquid, or gas.

label: cubic meter
definition: A volume unit which is equal to the volume of a cube with edges one meter in length. One cubic meter equals to 1000 liters.

label: cubic centimeter
definition: A volume unit which is equal to one millionth of a cubic meter or 10^[-9] m^[3], or to 1 ml.

label: milliliter
definition: A volume unit which is equal to one thousandth of a liter or 10^[-3] L, or to 1 cubic centimeter.

label: liter
definition: A volume unit which is equal to one thousandth of a cubic meter or 10^[-3] m^[3], or to 1 decimeter.

label: cubic decimeter
definition: A volume unit which is equal to one thousand of a cubic meter or 10^[-3] m^[3], or to 1 L.

label: microliter
definition: A volume unit which is equal to one millionth of a liter or 10^[-6] L.

label: nanoliter
definition: A volume unit which is equal to one thousandth of one millionth of a liter or 10^[-9] L.

label: picoliter
definition: A volume unit which is equal to 10^[-12] L.

label: femtoliter
definition: A volume unit which is equal to 10^[-15] L.

label: frequency unit
definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the number of repetitive actions in a particular time.

label: hertz
definition: A frequency unit which is equal to 1 complete cycle of a recurring phenomenon in 1 second.

label: force unit
definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the force is applied when a mass is accelerated.

label: newton
definition: A force unit which is equal to the force required to cause an acceleration of 1m/s2 of a mass of 1 Kg in the direction of the force.

label: pressure unit
definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the force applied to a given area.

label: pascal
definition: A pressure unit which is equal to the pressure or stress on a surface caused by a force of 1 newton spread over a surface of 1 m^[2].

label: energy unit
definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the work done by a certain force (gravitational, electric, magnetic, force of inertia, etc).

label: joule
definition: An energy unit which is equal to the energy required when a force of 1 newton moves an object 1 meter in the direction of the force.

label: power unit
definition: A unit which is a standard measure power or the rate of doing work.

label: watt
definition: A power unit which is equal to the power used when work is done at the rate of 1 joule per second.

label: illuminance unit
definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the luminous flux incident on a unit area.

label: lux
definition: An illuminance unit which is equal to the illuminance produced by 1 lumen evenly spread over an area 1 m^[2].

label: luminous flux unit
definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the flow of radiant energy.

label: lumen
definition: A luminous flux unit which is equal to the luminous flux emitted into 1 steradian by a point source of 1 candela.

label: catalytic activity unit
definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the amount of the action of a catalyst.

label: katal
definition: A catalytic unit activity which is equal to the activity of a catalyst in moles per second, such as the amount of an enzyme needed to transform one mole of substrate per second.

label: angle unit
definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the figure or space formed by the junction of two lines or planes.

label: plane angle unit
definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the angle formed by two straight lines in the same plane.

label: radian
definition: A plane angle unit which is equal to the angle subtended at the center of a circle by an arc equal in length to the radius of the circle, approximately 57 degrees 17 minutes and 44.6 seconds.

label: solid angle unit
definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the angle formed by three or more planes intersecting at a common point.

label: steradian
definition: A solid angle unit which is equal to the solid angle subtended at the center of a sphere by an area on the surface of the sphere that is equal to the radius squared.

label: radiation unit
definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the amount of radiation emitted by a given radiation source as well as the amount of radiation absorbed or deposited in a specific material by a radiation source.

label: activity (of a radionuclide) unit
definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the transformation (disintegration) rate of a radioactive substance.

label: absorbed dose unit
definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the energy imparted by ionizing radiation to unit mass of matter such as tissue.

label: dose equivalent unit
definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the expression of dose in terms of its biological effect.

label: exposure unit
definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the quantity that expresses the ability of radiation to ionize air and thereby create electric charges which can be collected and measured.

label: becquerel
definition: An activity (of a radionuclide) unit which is equal to the activity of a quantity of radioactive material in which one nucleus decays per second or there is one atom disintegration per second (dps).

label: curie
definition: An activity (of a radionuclide) unit which is equal to the activity of a quantity of radioactive material in which there are 3.7 x 10^[10] atom disintegration per second (dps).

label: gray
definition: An absorbed dose unit which is equal to the absorption of one joule of radiation energy by one kilogram of matter.

label: rad
definition: An absorbed dose unit which is equal to 0.01 gray (Gy).

label: roentgen
definition: An exposure unit which is equal to the amount of radiation required to liberate positive and negative charges of one electrostatic unit of charge in 1 cm^[3] of air at standard temperature and pressure (STP). This corresponds to the generation of approximately 2.0810^[9] ion pairs.

label: sievert
definition: A dose equivalent unit which is equal to the absorption of one joule of radiation energy by one kilogram of matter.

label: millisievert
definition: A dose equivalent unit which is equal to one thousandth of a sievert or 10^[-3] Sv.

label: microsievert
definition: A dose equivalent unit which is equal to one millionth of a sievert or 10^[-6] Sv.

label: Roentgen equivalent man
definition: A dose equivalent unit which when multiplied by hundred is equal to one sievert or 1 Sv. 1 Sv is equal to 100 rem.

label: microgray
definition: An absorbed dose unit which is equal to one millionth of a gray or 10^[-6] Gy.

label: milligray
definition: An absorbed dose unit which is equal to one thousandth of a gray or 10^[-3] Gy.

label: nanogray
definition: An absorbed dose unit which is equal to one thousandth of a millionth of a gray or 10^[-9] Gy.

label: nanosievert
definition: A dose equivalent unit which is equal to one thousandth of a millionth of a sievert or 10^[-9] Sv.

label: millicurie
definition: An activity (of a radionuclide) unit which is equal to one thousandth of a curie or 10^[-3] Ci.

label: microcurie
definition: An activity (of a radionuclide) unit which is equal to one millionth of a curie or 10^[-6] Ci.

label: disintegrations per minute
definition: An activity (of a radionuclide) unit which is equal to the activity of a quantity of radioactive material in which one nucleus decays per minute or there is one atom disintegration per minute.

label: counts per minute
definition: An activity (of a radionuclide) unit which is equal to the number of light emissions produced by ionizing radiation in one minute.

label: nanosecond
definition: A time unit which is equal to one thousandth of one millionth of a second or 10^[-9] s.

label: century
definition: A time unit which is equal to 100 years.

label: half life
definition: A time unit which represents the period over which the activity or concentration of a specified chemical or element falls to half its original activity or concentration.

label: foot candle
definition: An illuminance unit which is equal to the illuminance produced by 1 lumen evenly spread over an area 1 foot^[2]. One footcandle is equal to 10.76 lux.

label: irradiance unit
definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the power of electromagnetic radiation at a surface, per unit area.

label: watt per square meter
definition: An irradiance unit which is equal to 1 watt of radiant power incident per one square meter surface area.

label: einstein per square meter per second
definition: An irradiance unit which is equal to one einstein per square meter per second. One einstein is one mole of photons, regardless of their frequency. Therefore, the number of photons in an einstein is Avogadro's number.
exact_synonyms: mole per second and square meter mol/sm^2
einstein per square metre per second

label: light unit
definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the intensity of light.

label: watt per steradian per square meter
definition: A radiance unit which is equal to one watt of radiant power incident per steradian solid angle per one square meter projected area of the source, as viewed from the given direction.
exact_synonyms: watt per steradian per square metre

label: radiant intensity unit
definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the intensity of electromagnetic radiation.

label: microeinstein per square meter per second
definition: An irradiance unit which is equal to one microeinstein per square meter per second or 10^[-6] microeinstein/sm^[2].
exact_synonyms: microeinstein per square metre per second
micromole per second and square meter mmol/sm^2

label: radiance unit
definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the power of electromagnetic radiation through space or through a material medium in the form of electromagnetic waves.

label: watt per steradian
definition: A radiant intensity unit which is equal to one kilogram meter squared per second cubed per steradian.

label: mass percentage
definition: A dimensionless concentration unit which denotes the mass of a substance in a mixture as a percentage of the mass of the entire mixture.

label: mass volume percentage
definition: A dimensionless concentration unit which denotes the mass of the substance in a mixture as a percentage of the volume of the entire mixture.

label: volume percentage
definition: A dimensionless concentration unit which denotes the volume of the solute in mL per 100 mL of the resulting solution.

label: parts per notation unit
definition: A dimensionless concentration notation which describes the amount of one substance in another. It is the ratio of the amount of the substance of interest to the amount of that substance plus the amount of the substance.

label: parts per hundred
definition: A dimensionless concentration notation which denotes the amount of a given substance in a total amount of 100 regardless of the units of measure as long as they are the same.

label: parts per thousand
definition: A dimensionless concentration notation which denotes the amount of a given substance in a total amount of 1000 regardless of the units of measure as long as they are the same.

label: parts per million
definition: A dimensionless concentration notation which denotes the amount of a given substance in a total amount of 1,000,000 regardless of the units of measure used as long as they are the same or 1 part in 10^[6].

label: parts per billion
definition: A dimensionless concentration notation which denotes the amount of a given substance in a total amount of 1,000,000,000 regardless of the units of measure as long as they are the same or 1 part in 10^[9].

label: parts per trillion
definition: A dimensionless concentration notation which denotes the amount of a given substance in a total amount of 1,000,000,000 regardless of the units of measure used as long as they are the same or 1 part in 10^[12].

label: parts per quadrillion
definition: A dimensionless concentration notation which denotes the amount of a given substance in a total amount of 1,000,000,000,000 regardless of the units of measure used as long as they are the same or 1 part in 10^[15].

label: gram per milliliter
definition: A mass unit density which is equal to mass of an object in grams divided by the volume in milliliter.

label: kilogram per liter
definition: A mass unit density which is equal to mass of an object in kilograms divided by the volume in liters.

label: gram per liter
definition: A mass unit density which is equal to mass of an object in grams divided by the volume in liters.

label: milligram per milliliter
definition: A mass unit density which is equal to mass of an object in milligrams divided by the volume in milliliters.

label: unit per volume unit
definition: A concentration unit which is a standard measure of the number of units, as an agreed arbitrary amount, of a given substance per a specific volume of solution.

label: unit per milliliter
definition: A unit per milliliter unit which is equal to one unit of an agreed arbitrary amount per one milliliter.

label: unit per liter
definition: A unit per milliliter unit which is equal to one unit of an agreed arbitrary amount per one liter.

label: mass per unit volume
definition: A concentration unit which is a standard measure of the mass of a substance in a given volume (density).

label: enzyme unit
definition: A catalytic unit activity which is equal to the amount of the enzyme that catalyzes the conversion of 1 micro mole of substrate per minute.

label: density unit
definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the influence exerted by some mass.

label: linear density unit
definition: A density unit which is a standard measure of the mass exerting an influence on a one-dimensional object.

label: kilogram per meter
definition: An area density unit which is equal to the mass of an object in kilograms divided by one meter.

label: degree
definition: A plane angle unit which is equal to 1/360 of a full rotation or 1.7453310^[-2] rad.

label: dimensionless unit
definition: A unit which is a standard measure of physical quantity consisting of only a numerical number without any units.

label: percent
definition: A dimensionless ratio unit which denotes numbers as fractions of 100.

label: pi
definition: A dimensionless unit which denoted an irrational real number, approximately equal to 3.14159 which is the ratio of a circle's circumference to its diameter in Euclidean geometry.

label: count unit
definition: A dimensionless unit which denotes a simple count of things.

label: ratio unit
definition: A dimensionless unit which denotes an amount or magnitude of one quantity relative to another.

label: fraction
definition: A dimensionless ratio unit which relates the part (the numerator) to the whole (the denominator).

label: molecule count
definition: A dimensionless count unit which denotes the number of molecules.

label: purity percentage
definition: A dimensionless percent unit which denotes the homogeneity of a biomaterial.

label: confluence percentage
definition: A dimensionless percent unit which denotes the density of an attached or monolayer culture (e.g., cell culture).

label: degree Fahrenheit
definition: A temperature unit which is equal to 5/9ths of a kelvin. Negative 40 degrees Fahrenheit is equal to negative 40 degrees Celsius.

label: pH
definition: A dimensionless concentration notation which denotes the acidity of a solution in terms of activity of hydrogen ions (H+).

label: liter per kilogram
definition: A specific volume unit which is equal to one liter volume occupied by one kilogram of a particular substance.

label: milliliter per kilogram
definition: A specific volume unit which is equal to a thousandth of a liter per kilogram or 10^[-3] l/kg.

label: microliter per kilogram
definition: A specific volume unit which is equal to one millionth of a liter per kilogram or 10^[-6] l/kg.

label: cell concentration unit
definition: A concentration unit which denotes the average cell number in a given volume.

label: cells per milliliter
definition: A unit of cell concentration which is equal to one cell in a volume of 1 milliliter.

label: catalytic (activity) concentration unit
definition: A concentration unit which is a standard measure of the amount of the action of a catalyst in a given volume.

label: katal per cubic meter
definition: A catalytic (activity) concentration unit which is equal to 1 katal activity of a catalyst in a given volume of one cubic meter.

label: katal per liter
definition: A catalytic (activity) concentration unit which is equal to 1 katal activity of a catalyst in a given volume of one thousandth of a cubic meter.

label: volume per unit volume
definition: A dimensionless concentration unit which denotes the given volume of the solute in the total volume of the resulting solution.

label: milliliter per cubic meter
definition: A volume per unit volume unit which is equal to one millionth of a liter of solute in one cubic meter of solution.

label: milliliter per liter
definition: A volume per unit volume unit which is equal to one millionth of a liter of solute in one liter of solution.

label: gram per deciliter
definition: A mass density unit which is equal to mass of an object in grams divided by the volume in deciliters.

label: deciliter
definition: A volume unit which is equal to one tenth of a liter or 10^[-1] L.

label: colony forming unit
definition: A dimensionless count unit which a measure of viable bacterial numbers.

label: plaque forming unit
definition: A dimensionless count unit which a measure of plaque forming units in a given volume.

label: colony forming unit per volume
definition: A concentration unit which a measure of viable bacterial numbers in a given volume.

label: colony forming unit per milliliter
definition: A colony forming unit which a measure of viable bacterial numbers in one milliliter.

label: plaque forming unit per volume
definition: A concentration unit which a measure of plaque forming units in a given volume.

label: plaque forming unit per milliliter
definition: A concentration unit which a measure of plaque forming units in one milliliter.

label: disintegrations per second
definition: An activity (of a radionuclide) unit which is equal to the activity of a quantity of radioactive material in which one nucleus decays per second or there is one atom disintegration per second.

label: electric potential difference unit
definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the work done per unit charge as a charge is moved between two points in an electric field.

label: volt
definition: An electric potential difference unit which is equal to the work per unit charge. One volt is the potential difference required to move one coulomb of charge between two points in a circuit while using one joule of energy.

label: electric charge
definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the quantity of unbalanced electricity in a body (either positive or negative) and construed as an excess or deficiency of electrons.

label: coulomb
definition: An electrical charge unit which is equal to the amount of charge transferred by a current of 1 ampere in 1 second.

label: dalton
definition: An independently to the base SI units defined mass unit which is equal to one twelfth of the mass of an unbound atom of the carbon-12 nuclide, at rest and in its ground state.

label: kilodalton
definition: A mass unit which is equal to one thousand daltons.

label: watt-hour
definition: An energy unit which is equal to the amount of electrical energy equivalent to a one-watt load drawing power for one hour.

label: kilowatt-hour
definition: An energy unit which is equal to 1,000 watt-hours.

label: magnetic flux unit
definition: A unit which is a standard measure of quantity of magnetism, taking account of the strength and the extent of a magnetic field.

label: weber
definition: A magnetic flux unit which is equal to the amount of flux that when linked with a single turn of wire for an interval of one second will induce an electromotive force of one volt.

label: magnetic flux density unit
definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the strength of a magnetic field.

label: tesla
definition: A magnetic flux density unit which is equal to one weber per square meter.

label: volt-hour
definition: A magnetic flux unit which is equal to 3600 Wb.

label: kilovolt-hour
definition: A magnetic flux unit which is equal to one thousand volt-hours.

label: information unit
definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the amount of information.

label: bit
definition: An information unit which refers to a digit in the binary numeral system, which consists of base 2 digits (ie there are only 2 possible values: 0 or 1).

label: byte
definition: An information unit which is equal to 8 bits.

label: kilobyte
definition: An information unit which is equal to 1000 bytes.

label: megabyte
definition: An information unit which is equal to 1000 kB.

label: image resolution unit
definition: An information unit which is a standard measure of the detail an image holds.

label: chroma sampling unit
definition: An image resolution unit which is a standard measure of the amount of spatial detail in an image.

label: dynamic range unit
definition: An image resolution unit which is a standard measure of the amount of contrast available in a pixel.

label: spatial resolution unit
definition: An image resolution unit which is a standard measure of the way luminance and chrominance may be sampled at different levels.

label: dots per inch
definition: A spatial resolution unit which is a standard measure of the printing resolution, in particular the number of individual dots of ink a printer or toner can produce within a linear one-inch space.

label: micron pixel
definition: A spatial resolution unit which is equal to a pixel size of one micrometer.

label: pixels per inch
definition: A spatial resolution unit which is a standard measure of the resolution of a computer display, related to the size of the display in inches and the total number of pixels in the horizontal and vertical directions.

label: pixels per millimeter
definition: A spatial resolution unit which is a standard measure of the number of pixels in one millimeter length or width of a digital image divided by the physical length or width of a printed image.

label: base pair
definition: A count unit which contains one nucleotide.

label: kibibyte
definition: An information unit which is equal to 1024 B.

label: mebibyte
definition: An information unit which is equal to 1024 KiB.

label: millivolt
definition: An electric potential difference unit which is equal to one thousandth of a volt or 10^[-3] V.

label: kilovolt
definition: An electric potential difference unit which is equal to one thousand volts or 10^[3] V.

label: microvolt
definition: An electric potential difference unit which is equal to one millionth of a volt or 10^[-6] V.

label: nanovolt
definition: An electric potential difference unit which is equal to one billionth of a volt or 10^[-12] V.

label: picovolt
definition: An electric potential difference unit which is equal to one trillionth of a volt or 10^[-12] V.

label: megavolt
definition: An electric potential difference unit which is equal to one million volts or 10^[6] V.

label: surface tension unit
definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the ability of a liguid to attraction of molecules at its surface as a result of unbalanced molecular cohesive forces.

label: newton per meter
definition: A surface tension unit which is equal to one newton per meter.

label: dyne per cm
definition: A surface tension unit which is equal to one dyne per centimeter.

label: viscosity unit
definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the internal resistance of fluids to flow.

label: pascal second
definition: A viscosity unit which is equal to one pascale per second.

label: poise
definition: A viscosity unit which is equal to one dyne second per square centimeter.

label: decibel
definition: A ratio unit which is an indicator of sound power per unit area.

label: effective dose unit
definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the estimate of the stochastic effect that a non-uniform radiation dose has on a human.

label: conduction unit
definition: A unit which represents a standard measurement of the transmission of an entity through a medium.

label: electrical conduction unit
definition: A unit which represents a standard measurement of the movement of electrically charged particles through a transmission medium (electrical conductor).

label: heat conduction unit
definition: A unit which represents a standard measurement of the spontaneous transfer of thermal energy through matter, from a region of higher temperature to a region of lower temperature.

label: siemens
definition: An electrical conduction unit which is equal to A/V.

label: watt per meter kelvin
definition: An heat conduction unit which is equal to one watt divided by meter kelvin.

label: electronvolt
definition: A non-SI unit of energy (eV) defined as the energy acquired by a single unbound electron when it passes through an electrostatic potential difference of one volt. An electronvolt is equal to 1.602 176 53(14) x 10^-19 J.

label: electric field strength unit
definition: The electric field strength is a unit which is a measure of the potential difference between two points some distance apart.

label: volt per meter
definition: The volt per meter is a unit of electric field strength equal to the a potential difference of 1 volt existing between two points that are 1 meter apart.

label: absorbance unit
definition: A dimensionless logarithmic unit assigned to a measure of absorbance of light through a partially absorbing substance, defined as -log10(I/I_0) where I = transmitted light and I_0 = incident light.

label: volumetric flow rate unit
definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the volume of fluid which passes through a given surface per unit time .

label: microliters per minute
definition: A volumetric flow rate unit which is equal to one microliter volume through a given surface in one minute.

label: millimetres of mercury
definition: A unit of pressure equal to the amount of fluid pressure one millimeter deep in mercury at zero degrees centigrade on Earth.

label: milligram per liter
definition: A mass unit density which is equal to mass of an object in milligrams divided by the volume in liters.

label: microgram per milliliter
definition: A mass unit density which is equal to mass of an object in micrograms divided by the volume in millliters.

label: nanogram per milliliter
definition: A mass unit density which is equal to mass of an object in nanograms divided by the volume in milliliters.

label: amount per container
definition: A concentration unit which is a standard measure of the amount of a substance in a given container.

label: ug/disk
definition: A unit which is equal to one microgram per disk, where a disk is some physical surface/container upon which the substance is deposited.

label: nmole/disk
definition: A unit which is equal to one nanomole per disk, where a disk is some physical surface/container upon which the substance is deposited.

label: milliunits per milliliter
definition: A unit per milliliter unit which is equal to one thousandth of a unit of an agreed arbitrary amount per one milliliter.

label: rate unit
definition: A unit which represents a standard measurement occurrence of a process per unit time.

label: count per nanomolar second
definition: A rate unit which is equal to one over one nanomolar second.

label: count per molar second
definition: A rate unit which is equal to one over one molar second.

label: kilogram per hectare
definition: An area density unit which is equal to the mass of an object in kilograms divided by the surface area in hectares.

label: count per nanomolar
definition: A rate unit which is equal to one over one nanomolar.

label: count per molar
definition: A rate unit which is equal to one over one molar.

label: yotta
definition: A prefix in the metric system denoting a factor of ten to the power of 24.

label: hecto
definition: A prefix in the metric system denoting a factor of one hundred.

label: zetta
definition: A prefix in the metric system denoting a factor of ten to the power of 21.

label: exa
definition: A prefix in the metric system denoting a factor of ten to the power of 18.

label: peta
definition: A prefix in the metric system denoting a factor of ten to the power of 15.

label: tera
definition: A prefix in the metric system denoting a factor of ten to the power of 12.

label: giga
definition: A prefix in the metric system denoting a factor of ten to the power of 9.

label: mega
definition: A prefix in the metric system denoting a factor of million.

label: kilo
definition: A prefix in the metric system denoting a factor of one thousand.

label: deca
definition: A prefix in the metric system denoting a factor of ten.

label: deci
definition: A prefix in the metric system denoting a factor of one tenth.

label: milli
definition: A prefix in the metric system denoting a factor of one thousand.

label: centi
definition: A prefix in the metric system denoting a factor of one hundred.

label: micro
definition: A prefix in the metric system denoting a factor of 10 to the power of -6.

label: nano
definition: A prefix in the metric system denoting a factor of 10 to the power of -9.

label: microgram per liter
definition: A mass unit density which is equal to mass of an object in micrograms divided by the volume in liters.

label: pico
definition: A prefix in the metric system denoting a factor of 10 to the power of -12.

label: femto
definition: A prefix in the metric system denoting a factor of 10 to the power of -15.

label: atto
definition: A prefix in the metric system denoting a factor of 10 to the power of -18.

label: zepto
definition: A prefix in the metric system denoting a factor of 10 to the power of -21.

label: yocto
definition: A prefix in the metric system denoting a factor of 10 to the power of -24.

label: dose unit
definition: A concentration unit which is a standard measure of the amount of a toxic or pharmaceutical substance administered to a recipient subject, expressed in terms of the size of the subject.

label: milligram per kilogram
definition: A dose unit which is equal to 1 milligram of a toxic or pharmaceutical substance per kilogram body weight of the recipient subject.

label: milligram per square meter
definition: A dose unit which is equal to 1 milligram of a toxic or pharmaceutical substance per square meter of surface area of the recipient subject.

label: dosage unit
definition: A concentration unit which is a standard measure of the amount of a toxic or pharmaceutical substance administered over time to a recipient subject, expressed in terms of the size of the subject.

label: milligram per kilogram per day
definition: A dosage unit which is equal to 1 milligram per day of a toxic or pharmaceutical substance per kilogram body weight of the recipient subject.

label: relative light unit
definition: A derived unit which is a measure of relative light intensity, as typically measured by a luminometer, spectrophotometer, or fluorimeter in biological research applications.

label: relative luminescence unit
definition: A relative light unit which is a measure of relative luminescence intensity.

label: relative fluorescence unit
definition: A relative light unit which is a measure of relative fluorescence intensity.

label: turbidity unit
definition: A unit used to indicate the clarity of water or other solutions or suspensions, as measured by the ability of the solution or suspension to scatter light of a defined wavelength range.

label: cells per microliter
definition: A unit of cell concentration which is equal to one cell in a volume of 1 microliter.

label: cells per well
definition: A unit of cell concentration which is equal to 1 cell in a well or discrete container of arbitrary volume.

label: formazin nephelometric unit
definition: 1000 formazin turbidity units (FNU) on the empirical formazin turbidity scale represents reflectance of insol. reaction products of 0.0725 g hydrazine sulfate with 0.7250 g hexamethylenetetramine diluted to 1 L.

label: radioactivity concentration
definition: A concentration unit which is a standard measure of the amount of radioactivity in a given volume.

label: curie per liter
definition: A unit of radioactivity concentration which is equal to one curie in a volume of 1 liter.

label: microcurie per milliliter
definition: A unit of radioactivity concentration which is equal to one micro curie in a volume of 1 liter.

label: fold dilution
definition: A unit that is the ratio of concentration of two solutions of interest, typically with one solution derived from the other by the addition of solvent.

label: ton per hectare
definition: An area density unit which is equal to the mass of an object in tons divided by the surface area in hectares.

label: square angstrom
definition: An area unit which is equal to an area enclosed by a square with sides each 1 angstrom long.

label: megaHertz
definition: A frequency unit which is equal to one million hertz or 10^[6] V.

label: centiMorgan
definition: A unit used to express distances on a genetic map. In genetic mapping, distances between markers are determined by measuring the rate of meoitic recombination between them, which increases proportionately with the distance separating them. A cM is defined as the length of an interval in which there is a 1% probability of recombination. On the average, 1 cM is roughly equivalent to 1 megabase (Mb) of DNA, although this can vary widely due to hot and cold spots of recombination.

label: centiRay
definition: A unit of genetic map distance defined corresponding to an interval in which there is a 1% probability of X-irradiation induced breakage. To be completely specified, the unit must be qualified by the radiation in dosage in rads (e.g. cR8000), because this determines the actual breakage probability.

label: kilo base pair
definition: A unit equal to one thousand base pairs.

label: mega base pair
definition: A unit equal to one million base pairs

label: giga base pair
definition: A unit equal to one billion base pairs.

label: gigabyte
definition: An information unit which is equal to 1000000000 bytes.

label: terabyte
definition: An information unit which is equal to 1000 gigabytes.

label: square micrometer
definition: An area unit which is equal to an area enclosed by a square with sides each 1 micrometer long.

label: millisiemens
definition: An electrical conduction unit which is equal to one thousandth of a siemen or 10^[-3] siemens.

label: micromole per litre
definition: A specific concentration unit which is equal to 1 micromole in a given volume of one thousandth of a cubic meter.

label: micromole per kilogram
definition: A specific concentration unit which is equal to 1 micromole of a given substance per kilogram of solvent.

label: millimeters per day
definition: A speed/velocity unit which is equal to the speed of an object traveling 1 millimeter distance in one day.

label: ratio
definition: A dimensionless ratio unit which, given a pair of quantities a and b, for which b is a multiple of a, denotes b by giving the multiplier (coefficient) c for a to result in b.

label: volt-second per square centimeter
definition: An electrical mobility unit which is equal to one volt second per square centimeter.

label: kilometer per hour
definition: A speed/velocity unit which is equal to the speed of an object traveling 1 kilometer distance in one hour.

label: milli
definition: A mass unit which is equal to 1/12 the mass of 12C

label: hectare
definition: An area unit which is equal to an area of 10,000 square meters. Equivalent to 2.471 acres.

label: inch
definition: A length unit which is equal to 0.0254 metres.

label: thou
definition: A length unit which is equal to 0.0254 millimetres.

label: foot
definition: A length unit which is equal to 0.3048 metres, or 12 inches.

label: yard
definition: A length unit which is equal to 0.9144 metres, or 3 feet.

label: chain
definition: A length unit which is equal to 20.1168 metres, 66 feet, or 22 yards.

label: furlong
definition: A length unit which is equal to 20,116.8 metres, 660 feet, or 10 chains.

label: mile
definition: A length unit which is equal to 1,609.344 metres, or 8 furlongs.

label: league
definition: A length unit which is equal to 3 miles, or 4,828.032 metres

label: maritime length unit
definition: A maritime length unit is one used primarily at sea.

label: fathom
definition: A maritime length unit which is equal to 6.08 feet, or 1.853184 metres

label: cable
definition: A maritime length unit which is equal to 608 feet, 100 fathoms, or 185.3184 metres

label: nautical mile
definition: A maritime length unit which is equal to 6,080 feet, 10 cables, or 1,853.184 metres

label: perch
definition: An area unit which is equal to an area of 25.292,852,64 square meters, or 1 square rod.

label: rood
definition: An area unit which is equivalent to 1 furlong x 1 rod. This is equal to an area of 1,011.714,1056 square meters, or 40 square rods.

label: acre
definition: An area unit which is equivalent to 1 furlong x 1 chain. This is equal to an area of 4,046.856,4224 square meters, or 43,500 square feet.

label: fluid ounce
definition: An imperial volume unit which is equivalent to 28.413,0625 millilitres.

label: gill
definition: An imperial volume unit which is equivalent to 142.065,3125 millilitres.

label: pint
definition: An imperial volume unit which is equivalent to 568.261,25 millilitres.

label: quart
definition: An imperial volume unit which is equivalent to 1,136.5225 millilitres, or two pints.

label: gallon
definition: An imperial volume unit which is equivalent to 4,546.09 millilitres, or 8 pints.

label: grain
definition: An imperial mass unit which is equivalent to 64.798,91 milligrams.

label: drachm
definition: An imperial mass unit which is equivalent to 1.771,845,195,3125 grams, or 1/256 of 1 pound.

label: ounce
definition: An imperial mass unit which is equivalent to 28.349,523,125 grams, or 1/16 of 1 pound.

label: pound
definition: An imperial mass unit which is equivalent to 453.592,37 grams.

label: stone
definition: An imperial mass unit which is equivalent to 6,350.293,18 grams, or 14 pounds.

label: quarter
definition: An imperial mass unit which is equivalent to 12.700,586,36 kilograms, or 28 pounds.

label: hundredweight
definition: An imperial mass unit which is equivalent to 50.802,345,44 kilograms, 112 pounds, or 8 stone.

label: ton
definition: An imperial mass unit which is equivalent to 1,016.046,9088 kilograms, or 2,240 pounds.

label: slug
definition: An imperial gravitational unit which is equivalent to a mass that accelerates by 1ft/sÂ² when a force of one pound (lbf) is exerted on it.

label: teaspoon
definition: A metric teaspoon is a unit of measurement of volume widely used in cooking recipes and pharmaceutic prescriptions. It equals a 5mL volume.

label: united states customary teaspoon
definition: A United States customary units teaspoon is a unit of measurement of volume widely used in cooking recipes and pharmaceutic prescriptions in America. It equals a 4.93 mL volume.

label: tablespoon
definition: A metric tablespoon is a unit of measurement of volume widely used in cooking recipes and pharmaceutic prescriptions. It equals a 15mL volume.

label: australian metric tablespoon
definition: An Australian metric tablespoon is a unit of measurement of volume used in Australia for cooking recipes and pharmaceutic prescriptions. It equals a 20mL volume.

label: united states customary tablespoon
definition: A United States customary units tablespoon is a unit of measurement of volume widely used in cooking recipes and pharmaceutic prescriptions in America. It equals a 14.79 mL volume.

label: metric cup
definition: A metric cup is a unit of measurement of volume widely used in cooking recipes and pharmaceutic prescriptions. It equals a 250mL volume.

label: united states customary cup
definition: A United States customary units cup is a unit of measurement of volume widely used in cooking recipes and pharmaceutic prescriptions in America. It equals a 236.59 mL volume.

label: united states fda cup
definition: A United States FDA cup is a unit of measurement of volume used by the US Federal Department of Agriculture as a nutritional serving measure. It equals a 240 mL volume.

label: micromole
definition: DEPRECATED: Duplicate of http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UO_0000039. A substance unit which is equal to one millionth of a mole.

label: gram per square meter
definition: An area density unit which is equal to the mass of an object in grams divided by the surface area in meters squared.

label: nanogram per microliter
definition: A mass unit density which is equal to mass of an object in nanograms divided by the volume in microliters.

label: large calorie
definition: A unit of energy widely used in nutrition, equivalent to the amount of heat needed to cause one kilogram of water to rise in temperature by one degree Celsius.

label: pounds per square inch
definition: A pressure unit which is equal to 6894.757 pascal.

label: micrograms per wheaton bottle
definition: A unit of mass concentration defined as the number of micrograms of a substance per 250 ml Wheaton bottle.

label: picoampere
definition: An electric current unit current which is equal to one trillionth of an ampere or 10^[-12] A.

label: centigray
definition: An absorbed dose unit which is equal to 0.01 gray (Gy)

label: gigaelectronvolt
definition: A unit of energy that is equal to one thousand million electronvolts.

label: gigaelectronvolt per nucleon
definition: Derived unit which is equal to the total kinetic energy of an atomic nucleus in GeV divided by the number of nucleons in the nucleus

label: megaelectronvolt per nucleon
definition: Derived unit which is equal to the total kinetic energy of an atomic nucleus in MeV divided by the number of nucleons in the nucleus

label: kiloelectronvolt per micron
definition: A derived unit equal to the energy deposited by ionizing radiation per micron of path length in matter

label: gray per minute
definition: A derived absorbed dose unit which is equal to one gray absorbed per minute.

label: centigray per minute
definition: A derived absorbed dose unit which is equal to one centigray absorbed per minute.

label: milligray per minute
definition: A derived absorbed dose unit which is equal to one milligray absorbed per minute.

label: milligray per day
definition: A derived absorbed dose unit which is equal to one milligray absorbed per day.

label: milligray per hour
definition: A derived absorbed dose unit which is equal to one milligray absorbed per hour.

label: milligray per second
definition: A derived absorbed dose unit which is equal to one milligray absorbed per second.

label: kilometer
definition: A length unit which is equal to one thousand meters.

label: milligram per deciliter
definition: A mass unit density which is equal to mass of an object in milligrams divided by the volume in deciliters.

label: microgram per deciliter
definition: A mass unit density which is equal to mass of an object in micrograms divided by the volume in deciliters.

label: bar
definition: A pressure unit which is equal to 100,000 pascal or the pressure or stress on a surface caused by a force of 100,000 newtons spread over a surface of 1 m^[2].

label: picogram per milliliter
definition: A gram per milliliter unit which is equal to one picogram per one milliliter.

label: microgram per square centimeter
definition: An area density unit which is equal to the mass of an object in micrograms divided by the surface area in square centimeters.

label: microgram per microliter
definition: A mass unit density which is equal to mass of an object in nanograms divided by the volume in microliters.

label: cell count
definition: A count unit that denotes a count of cells.

label: heartbeats per minute
definition: A rate unit which represents a measurement of the number of an organism's heartbeats per one minute.

label: multiplicity of infection
definition: A ratio unit which denotes the quantity of infectious agents to infection targets.

label: breaths per minute
definition: A rate unit which represents a measurement of the number of breaths taken by an organism per one minute.

label: PCR quantification cycle
definition: A count unit of how many Polymerase Chain Reaction (PCR) cycles it took toÂ detect a real signalÂ from a sample. Equivalent to the PCR cycle number at which a sample's reaction curve intersects the threshold line.

label: titer
definition: A concentration unit which denotes the minimum amount of a substance in a solution that still yields a positive reading, as determined by serial dilution.
